pros:
A leading research and clinic community with a lot of excellent researchers;
Good benefit including vacation time, health insurance and retirement plan;
Space for personal development;
Access to broad educational resources.

cons:
* Seems to be losing its way with looming merger;
* Loyalty isn't valued. CEO/Director's mates seem to get senior roles which they are not qualified to do. I was given a form as an exit interview and no F2F despite 8+years service. Gives an idea of where the company's priorities lie. There's a huge push towards culture cleansing with an increased focus to push the older employees/culture out;
* Micro-managey culture, my current manager had shockingly poor managerial/organisational skills and believed in zero transparency

- Very unsupportive work environment with restrictive rules and lack of opportunities to speak up and improve ways of working;

- Sales employees are often "invisible" to the business and locally controlled in day-by-day tasks and activities;

- Progression is almost impossible - even if you have a strong background, the business doesn't explore your talent or even asks your feedback

- Completely obsolete methodologies, tools and processes, losing competitive advantage to several luxury online retailers.
